{
  "id": "exhaust-manufactured",
  "name": "Synthetic Exhaust",
  "desc": "Once exhaust becomes valuable, actors manufacture it deliberately: synthetic data, content farms, click farms, and preference manipulation. The byproduct becomes a product, and the provenance questions that follow undermine the original data market.",
  "picks": {
    "Capability Class": {
      "value": "Tool-grade",
      "memo": "Synthetic exhaust uses tool-grade systems because the manufacturing process relies on scalable automation rather than frontier analytical capability.",
      "detail": "Tool-grade capability is sufficient for exhaust manufacturing because the process depends on volume and automation, not analytical sophistication. Content farms and synthetic interaction generators do not need frontier models to produce plausible exhaust at scale. The tool-grade baseline demonstrates that synthetic exhaust is an accessibility problem, not a capability frontier problem. Lower capability systems can produce synthetic exhaust cheaply and at enormous volume."
    },
    "Domain Breadth": {
      "value": "General",
      "memo": "Synthetic exhaust spans general domains because content farms and synthetic generators produce data across every topic to maximize coverage and market value.",
      "detail": "General breadth means synthetic exhaust covers every domain where genuine exhaust has market value. The manufacturers produce synthetic interaction data across topics to match the coverage profile of authentic exhaust datasets. General coverage makes synthetic exhaust harder to distinguish from genuine exhaust through domain-specific analysis. Domain breadth in synthetic exhaust mirrors the general character of the genuine exhaust it imitates."
    },
    "Capability Trajectory": {
      "value": "Rapid",
      "memo": "Rapid capability trajectory makes synthetic exhaust harder to detect because improving generation quality outpaces improving detection and verification methods.",
      "detail": "Rapid trajectory means synthetic content generation improves faster than authenticity detection capabilities. Each generation of language models makes synthetic exhaust more convincing and harder to distinguish from genuine interaction data. The rapid improvement creates an arms race between manufacturers and authenticators that manufacturers are currently winning. Rapid trajectory is what makes synthetic exhaust a persistent and worsening problem rather than a temporary challenge."
    },
    "Research Automation": {
